    Date(s) Tested  : 2024-08-09
    Tested By       : Latrice Postell
    Systems Tested  : Windows Server 2019 Datacenter, Build 1809, Windows Pro 10 
    PowerShell Ver. : 5.1.17763.6189


WN10-CC-000005 - Camera access from the lock screen must be disabled.

1. Tenable Discovered STIGS FAILURE WN10-CC-000005
Registry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE
Registry Path: \SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\Personalization\

Value Name: NoLockScreenCamera

Value Type: REG_DWORD
Value: 1
2. Followed advice given from Tenanble in the Check cololum
3.There is no path \Personalization\ so it was created with powershell. Below is the code use to create path:
$regPath = "HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\Personalization\"
$name = "NoLockScreenCamera"
$value = 1

# Create path if it doesn't exist
if (-not (Test-Path $regPath)) {
Â    New-Item -Path $regPath -Force | Out-Null
4. Set the value to 1 with powershell code below:
# Set the value
Set-ItemProperty -Path $regPath -Name $name -Value $value -Type DWord
5. Restarted the computer and check if value was there. The value was there
6. Run Tenable and WN10-CC-000005 passed
